    <thetext>Description of problem:

Due to Apache bug #53555, `systemctl reload httpd` will cause problems with some configurations. A full stop and start of the service is required to work around the problem.

`/etc/logrotate.d/httpd` calls `systemctl reload httpd` as past of post-rotate. This can result in thousands upon thousands of errors like the below, and it will lead to the httpd service to become unavailable after a few minutes if the service is configured with TLS.

    AH00485: scoreboard is full, not at MaxRequestWorkers

I’ve tested versions 2.4.18 and 2.4.23. More info in Apache bugzilla #53555.

Because of this problem, `/etc/logrotate.d/httpd` should run `systemctl stop httpd` followed by `systemctl start httpd` instead of reload (or restart).</thetext>
